<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Law for Emission Control in Offing: Pak Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan is formulating a new
comprehensive law for control of emission to improve environment
and fight pollution in the country.
</P>
<P>
The new law will be passed by the National Assembly in its
forthcoming session, said Minister for Food, Agriculture and
Environment Syeda Abida Hussain in Lahore, capital city of
Pakistan's eastern Punjab province, a day before the International
Earth Day.
</P>
<P>
Abida said that the new law, which is presently under the
consideration of the National Assembly, will cover all the aspects
relating to environment and pollution.
</P>
<P>
She said that every type of pollution, including noise
pollution, would be covered in this law.
</P>
<P>
Abida said a Citizen Complaint Service will also be set up
under the new law, which will ensure the implementation of the law
and receive complaints about any violation of the law.
</P>
<P>
She said that a national conservation strategy was also being
finalized and there was close cooperation with the provinces in
this regard to evolve a better strategy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
