<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Price Rebounds to 17.17 Dollars a Barrel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The average price of OPEC's basket
of seven crude oils rebounded to 17.17 U.S. dollars per barrel
last week, the Vienna-based OPEC Secretariat said today.
</P>
<P>
A week earlier, the average price for OPEC's basket of seven
crudes fell to 16.91 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the low price should be blamed on the advent of
warmer weather and the decline of crude oil demands from the
Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD)
members and former Soviet republics.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the return of Iraq to the oil export market and the
increase of oil recovered in the global sphere also contributed to
the sustained plunge of price since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
The price will remain fluctuating, experts added.
</P>
<P>
The average price of OPEC crude oil was as high as 23.19
dollars per barrel last January, but fell sharply to 20.48 dollars
a month later.
</P>
<P>
In March, it fell to 18.64 dollars, far below OPEC's benchmark
price of 21 dollars per barrel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
