<HEADLINE> Bosnian-Serbian Summit Reportedly to Be Held Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, April 21 (Xinhua) -- A summit between the chairman of
the Bosnian Presidency Alija Izetbegovic and Serbian President
Slobodan Milosevic could take place within a month.
</P>
<P>
Preparations for the summit is underway and the venue would be
somewhere in Croatia, Kasim Trnka, Bosnia's ambassador to Croatia,
was quoted as saying by a report in the Belgrade Daily Nasa Borba
available here today.
</P>
<P>
Trnka said the summit would be aimed at establishing diplomatic
relations between Bosnia and Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Bosnian Ministry of Foreign Affairs had reportedly
evaluated a draft agreement on the bilateral relations presented
by the Yugoslav side and the document would be sent to the Bosnian
Presidency for its consideration.
</P>
<P>
The process of normalizing ties between the two countries has
been bogged down for Belgrade's requirement that Bosnia should
withdraw its lawsuit against Yugoslavia on the International Court
of Justice in the Hague, the Netherlands. The Bosnian side has
insisted on unconditional installation of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
There are no clear indications yet as to how the issue could be
settled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
