<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak Attracts 350M Dollar Foreign Investment in 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan has attracted 350.1
million U.S. dollars of foreign direct investment during the first
half of the current financial year which will end on June 30,
sources from the Board of Investment said here today.
</P>
<P>
And the portfolio investment in the country has amounted to
141.1 million dollars during the same period.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, the largest investment has been made
by the United Kingdom, which is to the tune of 198.2 million
dollars including 166.4 million dollars of direct investment and
portfolio investment of 31.8 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
It is followed by the United States whose direct investment
totaled 107 million dollars while portfolio investment amounted to
48.3 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
During the year 1995-96 Pakistan attracted total foreign
investment of 1.296 billion dollars which included 1.091 billion
dollars of direct investment and portfolio investment of 205.2
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The United Kingdom was the biggest investor with total
investment of 385.9 million dollars, out of which direct
investment shared 317.8 million dollars and portfolio investment
amounted to 68.1 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The United States stood second with a total of 355.7 million
dollars of investment including direct investment of 319.8 million
dollars and portfolio investment of 35.9 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Barring the year 1995-96, the average foreign direct investment
in Pakistan during the last five years totaled around 335 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, with the exception of the year 1994-95, in which the
portfolio investment touched an all time high of 1.090 billion,
the last five years saw an average of around 165 million dollars
of portfolio investment.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the government was making every effort to
boost the flow of direct foreign investment into Pakistan and
hoped that incentives recently announced in the Economic Reform
Package by the government would give an impetus to the investment
flow into the country.
</P>
<P>
Efforts were vigorously made to provide a one-window operation
to foreign investors through the Board of Investment, the sources
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
