<HEADLINE> Iranian Pilot Killed in Helicopter Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 21 (Xinhua) -- A helicopter crashed 50
kilometers west of the Iranian capital city of Tehran at 13:45
local time (10:15 GMT) today, killing its pilot, Iran's official
news agency IRNA reported today.
</P>
<P>
The reported said that there was no passenger on board the
ill-fated helicopter.
</P>
<P>
This is the third aircraft mishap in the country in the past
four months.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the helicopter belonging to the National
Iranian Oil Company (NIOC) was on a routine flight from the town
of Karaj on the outskirts of Tehran to the city of Isfahan in
central Iran.
</P>
<P>
The NIOC experts rushed to the scene of the crash to
investigate the cause of the mishap.
</P>
<P>
The IRNA report indicated that technical failure had caused
the crash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
