<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Sets Wheat Target at 19M Tons for 1997-98 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government has
set a target of 19 million tons of wheat for 1997-98 fiscal year
in order to achieve self sufficiency in the food sector.
</P>
<P>
The government led by Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif has already
announced a package for the agriculture sector which makes the
target possible to be achieved, sources from the Ministry of Food
and Agriculture said today.
</P>
<P>
The main attraction of the agriculture package is the increase
in support prices of wheat, rice and other agricultural products.
</P>
<P>
The package is expected to encourage farmers to bring more area
under wheat cultivation and grow more wheat, the sources believed.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the government is confident to achieve the
target for wheat crop in the next fiscal year as the other
measures announced in the agriculture package envisages the
reduction of different taxes on some output used in the
agricultural sector which will not only enhance the wheat
production, but also the production of other major crops.
</P>
<P>
The target of wheat production for the current fiscal year is
17 million tons while the total requirement for the commodity in
Pakistan is around 19.4 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's agricultural sector is expected to attain a growth
rate of 5.7 percent in the next fiscal year as against an
estimated growth of 1.9 percent in 1996-97 fiscal year, according
to the sources.  
</P>
