<HEADLINE> Coming Africa Tour to Boost Friendship: Premier (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said here
today that his upcoming visit to Africa is aimed at reinforcing
mutual understanding and cooperation with the African countries
and advancing their long-time friendship.
</P>
<P>
Li will pay an official goodwill visit to Zambia, Mozambique,
Gabon, Cameroon, Nigeria and Tanzania from May 5-14 at the
invitations of state leaders of the six African countries. He will
also pay a working visit to Seychelles from May 3-4 as guest of
the government of Seychelles.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting today with Ambassadors to China from the six
countries, Li reiterated that China and Africa are reliable
friends with a history of friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese and African people share the same or similar
historical experiences, and under the current new world situation,
both are faced with the task of safeguarding peace and seeking
development, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and African countries, though far apart
geographically, are all developing countries, and their friendship
has stood the test of time in spite of the changing world
situation.
</P>
<P>
They have carried out broad and fruitful cooperation in
political, economic, cultural and other sectors, and closely
coordinated with each other on international issues based on the
five principles of peaceful co-existence, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decades, he said, exchanges of high-level visits
between China and African countries have been frequent, with
Chinese leaders visiting dozens of African countries and more than
100 leaders from over 40 African countries touring China.
</P>
<P>
Li said that last May, President Jiang Zemin visited Africa,
and put forward the proposal of establishing the long-term
friendly, comprehensive Sino-African relations oriented to the
21st century, which was well received by the African countries and
people.
</P>
</TEXT>
