<HEADLINE> Iranian Students Stage Anti-German Demonstrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of Iranian students
staged anti-German demonstrations in front of the German Embassy
here today to condemn a Berlin court verdict accusing Iranian
leaders of involving in a assassination case in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that these students
are children of martyrs who were killed in the eight-year
war between Iran and Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Some of the demonstrators carried placards which read:
"German government, this is a political game", "the Berlin
court is nothing but a worthless mockery of justice" and "the
German judicial officials proved that they are strongly under
influence of Zionists".
</P>
<P>
The report said that the demonstrations were held in a
peaceful way and there was no violence.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators issued a resolution before they ended their
rally.
</P>
<P>
Tehran-Bonn relations have strained since earlier this month
when a Berlin court investigating the assassination of four
Kurdish opposition leaders in Mykonos restaurant in Berlin in
September 1992, accused Iranian supreme leadership of ordering the
assassination.
</P>
<P>
The Berlin court verdict also sparked a diplomatic battle
between European Union member nations and Iran. Both of them
have recalled their ambassadors. Bonn and Tehran also expelled
four diplomatic from each side. 
</P>
</TEXT>
