<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Calls for Technological Advancement for Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo
today called on the country's state-owned enterprises to speed up
technological advancement in order to raise production efficiency
and better adapt themselves to the market.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar on industrial technological progress,
attended by ministerial and provincial officials, as well as heads
of some giant state-run enterprises, Wu affirmed the role of
technological progress in promoting the sustained, rapid and
healthy development of the national economy over the past several
years.
</P>
<P>
"It is key to the survival, development and competitiveness of
enterprises," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He urged the local and department officials and business heads
to take the lead in studying the market mechanism so as to avoid
repetitious construction projects.
</P>
<P>
They are also encouraged to find funds on their own for
investment in technological renovations, "instead of depending
solely on the central government," said the vice-premier.
</P>
<P>
Wu also urged state enterprises to work together for this
purpose.
</P>
<P>
Top leaders of governments at various levels must pay close
attention to this drive, and the legal person shall be fully
responsible for their technical renovation projects, Wu stressed.
</P>
<P>
He is a member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee
of the Chinese Communist Party. The seminar was jointly sponsored
by the State Administration College and the State Economic and
Trade Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
