<HEADLINE> European Shares Mixed, London Up for 5th Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Europe's major stock markets ended
mixed today, with London closing higher for the fifth day running
and Paris down sharply on political and economic uncertainties.
</P>
<P>
British shares on the London market, Europe's largest, had a
good day and ended well up, with the FTSE 100 index 18.2 points up
at 4,328.7, although trade volumes were thin.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that worries over higher interest rates and the
outcome of the general election on May 1 were offset by the
impressive debut performance of Britain's newest bank Alliance &AMP;
Leicester.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that many investors have now moved to the
sidelines to await the outcome of next week's general election.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, German shares moved off early lows to finish the
session barely ahead, as the weak dollar and fears of a fuel tax
rise weighed on autos, with the DAX-30 index, having hit a low of
3,306.15, 3.19 points higher at 3,347.58 by the time of close.
</P>
<P>
The Paris bourse suffered heavy losses and closed sharply lower
amid expectations that President Jacques Chirac will call an early
general election, with the CAC-40 index down 24.89 points at
2,522.67.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE-100 index of leading British shares ended up 18.2
points at 4,328.7. The Frankfurt DAX-30 index finished 3.19 points
higher at 3,347.58. The Paris CAC-40 index closed 24.89 points
down at 2,522.67. 
</P>
