<HEADLINE> Iran Vows Not to Change Policy Despite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Supreme Leader Ayatollah
Ali Khamenei stated here today that the United States can never
force Iran to change its foreign policy by subjecting it to
conspiracies such as the Mykonos case.
</P>
<P>
Ali Khamenei, who is also Commander-in-Chief of the Iranian
Armed Forces, made the statement on the eve of the three-day
maneuvers code-named "Path of Jerusalem" in the southern port
city of Bandar Abbas, about 1,300 kilometers south of the
capital city Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the maneuvers
will be launched in Iran's four provinces this evening in the
presence of Khamenei.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei said that the United States and Israel had tried hard
to subject the Iranian government and its people to "what they
call isolation" and separate Iran from Europe and Asia by using
Germany in the Mykonos case.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, "They did not succeed in their conspiracy
and they will never succeed."
</P>
<P>
"The Berlin court announced on April 10 a verdict of the 1992
assassination of four Iranian-Kurdish dissidents in the Berlin
Mykonos restaurant, charging Iranian top leaders with ordering
the killing.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian leader also urged his people, particularly the
youths, to try to neutralize the negative impact of hostile
foreign propaganda.
</P>
<P>
However, he noted, no "real or serious dangers" are
undermining the country's borders at the moment. Nevertheless, the
Iranian people should be aware of and watchful over them.
</P>
<P>
The relations between Iran and the United States have been
strained since the two countries broke off diplomatic ties on
April 7, 1980 in the wake of U.S. hostage crisis over which Iran
was accused of masterminding the abduction.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has pursued the dual-containment policy against Iran
and imposed sanctions and embargoes on Iran on the charges of
seeking weapons of mass destruction, sponsoring terrorism and
opposing the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier General Rahim Safavi, Deputy Commander of the Islamic
Revolution's Guards Corps (IRGC), said that 200,000 IRGC men and
volunteer forces will take part in the war games to be held in
Hormuzgan, Bushehr, Khuzestan and Kermanshah provinces in
southern, southwestern and western Iran.
</P>
<P>
He said that the maneuvers are part of the routine war games,
which feature various operations including missile, air, sea and
land operations.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the war games will be of the defensive
nature, during which surface-to-air, surface-to-sea and
surface-to-surface missiles will be tested in the games.
</P>
<P>
He said that Iran has no intention of committing any act of
aggression on any other country but has the capability to counter
any of such moves. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
