<HEADLINE> China's Top Tractor Maker to List in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUOYANG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The China First Tractor and
Construction Machinery Corporation, the largest farm-machinery
builder in the country, is busy preparing for its upcoming listing
on the Hong Kong stock market.
</P>
<P>
The group, which mainly produces farm tractors along with
automobiles and engineering machinery, is among the 38 firms
selected by the authorities to list overseas this year, and is
expected to issue H shares on the Hong Kong United Exchange later
this year.
</P>
<P>
Dong Yong'an, deputy general manager of the corporation, told
Xinhua in a recent interview that the company plans to combine the
would-be listed company with a dozen of its workshops and
departments that are directly engaged in the manufacturing of
tractors.
</P>
<P>
The board of directors of the proposed listed firm will be its
top decision-maker, though the corporation is to be its largest
stockholder, according to the deputy general manager.
</P>
<P>
China is a major grain producer in the world and grain
production is of great significance to the stability and
development of the country, Dong said.
</P>
<P>
He said the government has focused much attention on the farm
machinery industry, as its growth has a direct bearing on the
country's agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, government investment has been increased in
both the agricultural sector and the farm machinery manufacturing
industry. Meanwhile, prosperous farmers have shown enthusiasm for
purchasing tractors and other farm machines, according to Dong.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming listing is likely to have a positive influence
on the country's farm machinery industry.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the corporation turned out some 150,000 tractors of
various types, some with horsepower ranging from 15 to 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
