<HEADLINE> New System to Administer Graphic Design Archive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Qinghua University, China's top
technical institution of higher learning, has newly developed a
system to administer graphic design archives, marking a change in
the traditional method of hand-drawn designs.
</P>
<P>
The high-tech system combines the most advanced techniques
available from Qinghua, Intergraph and Micron, according to the
developer, the Qinghua Unisplendour Group run by Qinghua
University.
</P>
<P>
With the new system, engineering designs will no longer have to
be drawn by hand, which liberates designers from the drawing board.
</P>
<P>
The system was announced here today in a meeting focusing on
the application of computer-aided design (CAD) technology.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the application of the graphic design computer
program will also give impetus to the popularity of CAD technology
in China.
</P>
<P>
CAD is a main element of electronic information technology, and
a fundamental technology needed for the build-up of the
information sector.
</P>
<P>
CAD is rapidly becoming widespread in China, but the main
software still needs to be imported from overseas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
