<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng met with
Chairman of the Kazakhstan Lower House Marat Ospanov here today,
saying that China is ready to work with the central Asia nation to
build a comprehensive cooperative partnership facing the 21st
century on the basis of the five principles of peaceful
co-existence.
</P>
<P>
Li said that in the five years since the two countries set up
diplomatic ties, exchange of visits by high-ranking officials
between the two sides has been frequent, mutual understanding and
trust have been deepened and cooperation in all fields expanded.
</P>
<P>
