<HEADLINE> Football Hooligan Suspects Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Ten suspected football hooligans
were arrested in dawn raids on Tuesday after a month-long
investigation into crowd violence at an English Division One match.
</P>
<P>
The raids, codenamed Operation Wildcard, were carried out by
detectives from west London who investigated crowd trouble at last
month's match between Queen's Park Rangers and Portsmouth.
</P>
<P>
Police identified suspects' faces from videos of the crowd
before swooping on the fans, mostly Portsmouth supporters, who
were taken into custody at Hammersmith police station.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,900 pornographic videos were seized from one
address and a shotgun -- suspected to be unlicensed -- and 31
rounds of ammunition were found at another. 
</P>
</TEXT>
