<HEADLINE> HK Becomes World's 7th Largest Trading Entity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong had ascended in the
world ranking of trade to become the seventh largest trading
entity in merchandise trade in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The ranking was calculated on the basis of figures released in
a report, "Overview of World Trade in 1996 and the Outlook for
1997" published by the World Trade Organization (WTO) earlier this
month.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong had been the eighth largest trading entity since
1993.
</P>
<P>
As regards commercial services trade, Hong Kong had also moved
one place up to become the world's 10th largest commercial
services trading entity in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Director-General of Trade Alan Lai expressed here today his
welcome to the ascendance of Hong Kong's ranking concerning trade
and commercial services.
</P>
<P>
Lai said, "Hong Kong's ascendancy on the world trade league
table demonstrates further the benefits of Hong Kong's strict
adherence to the free trade principles."
</P>
<P>
He said, "Hong Kong is a staunch supporter of free trade. We
will continue to practice this policy and actively participate in
the multilateral and regional fora to pursue the further
liberalization in trade in goods and services," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
