<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Meets Finnish Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislator Qiao Shi
told visiting Finnish Defense Minister Anneli Taina that the two
countries should develop their relationship on the basis of the
Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence.
</P>
<P>
In today's meeting with Taina, who is the first Finnish defense
minister to visit China since diplomatic relations were forged,
Qiao said that Finland also is one of the first Western nations to
set up diplomatic ties with China, and that bilateral relations in
various areas have been good in recent years.
</P>
<P>
China respects the policies made by Finland, which are in
keeping with its own national characteristics, he noted.
</P>
<P>
At Tiana's request, Qiao briefed her on China's position on the
human rights issue.
</P>
<P>
He said that China proposes to increase dialogue, not
confrontation, in the human rights issue, noting that it is normal
to have different views on the subject.
</P>
<P>
"This issue should be settled through dialogue," he said. "And
it is better for each country to handle this matter on its own."
</P>
<P>
China opposes certain powers engaging in confrontation with
China and interfering in its internal affairs concerning this
issue, he stated.
</P>
<P>
"More and more countries have come to realize that
confrontation is not the way to solve the problems, and dialogue
is better than confrontation," he noted.
</P>
<P>
With unique characteristics, China opposes hegemonism and power
politics, holds that each nation should be equal, no matter how
big or small, rich or poor, powerful or weak, and should not
interfere in each other's internal affairs, he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
"Differences can only be handled through discussion on an equal
footing," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Speaking highly of China's economic achievement, Taina said the
country has scored progress in economic and social fields.
</P>
<P>
She noted that the two countries should deepen mutual
understanding through increased exchanges, adding that sound
bilateral relations can create a favorable atmosphere for holding
talks between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Taina said that she hopes Finland and China will further
advance their friendly and cooperative relations in all areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
