<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Telecom to Offer High-speed Digital Data Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong Telecom today signed a
memorandum of understanding with AT&AMP;T to provide a high-speed
digital international private line service which will benefit
Internet Service Providers, financial institutions and other
multinational companies.
</P>
<P>
According to Hongkong Telecom, transmission speed of the new
service will reach 44.737 Mbps and marks the first such agreement
for high speed, high-bandwidth transmission between Hong Kong and
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Hongkong Telecom International and AT&AMP;T
are responsible for the development of the network architecture so
that proper maintenance, testing provisioning, service performance
and other related issues will be addressed.
</P>
<P>
In addition, both parties will provide the necessary technical
modifications and share management of the international portion of
their respective services. Work on the service is expected for
completion by the third quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Alistair Grieve, deputy Chief Executive, said that the
agreement clearly signifies Hongkong Telecom's commitment to
enhancing the territory's international connectivity which
reinforces Hong Kong's position as the hub of Asia.
</P>
<P>
He said that the new service will help meet the needs of
customers for high speed transmission and it enables multinational
business to send and receive large amounts of digital data at
speeds of up to 45 million bits per second, the equivalent of
transmitting the contents of a set of encyclopedia once every 15
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Typical service applications include Internet, multimedia,
video imaging and LAN-to-LAN interconnection, and CAD/CAM.
</P>
</TEXT>
