<HEADLINE> Hong Kong To Open New Cross Harbor Tunnel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A third cross harbor tunnel
which links the Kowloon Peninsula and the Hong Kong Island is to
be opened at the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
With a designed capacity of handling 180,000 vehicles a day,
the Western Harbor Tunnel is expected to ease the traffic
congestion cross the Victoria Harbor.
</P>
<P>
The two existing crossings, the Cross Harbor Tunnel and the
Eastern Harbor Tunnel, each with two lanes, are now capable of
handling a total of 200,000 to 210,000 vehicles a day.
</P>
<P>
When putting into operation on April 30, the 2-km tunnel will
add six lanes and boost the cross-harbor traffic capacity by 75
percent, said Robert Adams, chairman of the Western Harbor Tunnel
Company Limited.
</P>
<P>
The tunnel is estimated to take in 50,000 to 70,000 vehicles a
day at the initial stage of operation and may reach its full
capacity in ten years.
</P>
<P>
The new tunnel, connecting Sai Ying Pun on the west of Hong
Kong Island and the southern end of the West Kowloon Reclamation,
is at the conjunction point of several trunk expressways,
including the one westwards to the New Airport being constructed
at Chek Lop Kok.
</P>
<P>
Actually, the Western Harbor Crossing is the only privately
funded project out of the ten Airport Core Programs.
</P>
<P>
It took nearly three years to complete the Western Harbor
Tunnel, which cost 7.5 billion HK dollars (about 1 billion US
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
