<HEADLINE> Australian dollar Falls Due to Wage Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A controversial wage claim by
the trade unions was rejected by the Australian Industrial
Relations Commission  (AIRC) today, that left the Australian
dollar 15 cents lower.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 77.59 US cents down from 77.74
at Monday's close.
</P>
<P>
The wage claim had been a source of concern to the Reserve Bank
of Australia, as having the potential to increase inflationary
pressures through boosting wages growth.
</P>
<P>
In its findings today, the AIRC cited the Reserve Bank's
concerns and granted a 10 Australian dollars (7.8 US dollars) a
week flat increase, compared to the unions' 20 Australian dollars
(15.6 US dollars) a week claim.
</P>
<P>
On today's cross-rates, the Australian dollar was at 97.61 yen
from 97.47 yen against the Japanese yen and was at 1.3211 marks
from 1.3248 marks against the German mark.  
