<HEADLINE> Macao Mobile Phone Subscribers Reach 44,600 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The number of mobile phone users in
 Macao increased to 44,669 in 1996, up 22 percent from that in
1995, the Macao Telecommunications Company (CTM) said in an
annual report.
</P>
<P>
CTM established a total of 161,485 telephone lines by the end
of last year following the company's operation in 1981. That means
 one telephone for fewer than three residents in the territory.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Macao residents' long-distance calls added up to 1.8
million hours, up 3.7 percent from 1995, according to the report
issued on Monday.
</P>
<P>
As a result, CTM made a total profit of 273.9 million patacas
(about 34.67 million U.S. dollars), an increase of 3 percent from
1995.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the report said the value of the company's total
assets amounted to 1.738 billion patacas (about 220 million
dollars), with investment exceeding 2.5 billion patacas (about 316
 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
CTM plans to invest 350 million patacas this year in
telecommunications equipment and laying of submarine cables,
according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
