<HEADLINE> Pakistan Needs 1 Billion Dollars for Wheat Import: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan needs to mobilize
additional one billion U.S. dollars during the current calendar
year to import wheat to meet the national demand, local news paper
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan has to import about 4 million tons of wheat to bridge
the gap that is expected to emerge in the next 12 months, said the
report.
</P>
<P>
The new crop, the harvesting of which has already been started,
is estimated at around 15-16 million tons against a total demand
for 20 million tons, it said.
</P>
<P>
The report suggested that one of the best way of getting out of
the wheat crisis is to increase the acreage of wheat cultivation
and use good-quality seed to improve per acre yield.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan has been facing an acute wheat flour shortage for a
few months. Millions of people have been affected by the wheat
shortage brewing since the middle of January this year.
</P>
<P>
There have been incidents in the last few weeks of angry
citizens looting utility stores and even snatching flour bags from
the government trucks and private shops.  
</P>
