<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Strive for Trade Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam had been attaching special
attention to the process of accession to the World Trade
Organization (WTO), said a senior official on Monday in Ho Chi
Minh City.
</P>
<P>
"The economic integration is the prevailing trend in the
world," said Trade Minister Le Van Triet, stressing that only by
enhancing the competitiveness of the national economy could
Vietnam economically catch up with other countries in the region
and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
While referring to the protection of the country's infant
agricultural and industrial sectors, Triet said that some
exceptional measures may be applied to safeguard domestic
enterprises and products.
</P>
<P>
"Gradually enhancing the competitiveness through international
economic integration is the strategic direction adopted by the
party and the government at this stage of development," he added.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that Vietnam must achieve a high and
sustainable growth rate so as to catch up with other members of
the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) in the coming
years.
</P>
<P>
"If the annual growth rate of ASEAN in the coming years is six
to seven percent, the growth rate of Vietnam should be nine to ten
percent so that the country will achieve the same level of
development as that of neighboring countries in the next 30
years," said the minister. 
</P>
