<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Hungary to Strengthen Economic Links </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Hungarian Prime
Minister Gyula Horn said today that his government would like
Malaysian companies to participate in the development of Hungary's
infrastructure, tourism and industrial park projects.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference here at the end of his two-day
official visit to Malaysia, he said that due to the low level of
trade ties between the two countries, the establishment of a
Malaysian trade office for export promotion in Hungary had been
initiated.
</P>
<P>
He also said links in various fields such as sports, education
and culture should be expanded, expecting a more active Malaysian
participation in English language training courses in Hungary and
that some sort of an agreement be reached on the mutual
recognition of university diplomas and degrees.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian leader said direct air links between Budapest and
Kuala Lumpur should also be established.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Hungary and Malaysia signed an agreement on
scientific and technological cooperation and a Memorandum of
Understanding (MOU) on trade promotion cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Horn, who arrived here Monday, will leave here later today.
