<HEADLINE> Chinese State Loan to Support Joint Venture Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Bank, one of
China's three policy-oriented banks, will provide 300 million yuan
in loans to a joint venture that will produce a much-needed
component of polyester fiber.
</P>
<P>
PTA, which is a basic ingredient in polyester fiber and other
polyester products, is in high demand in China and the
Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The new venture will be located in a heavy industrial zone in
southern Zhuhai city, in south China's Guangdong province and will
be set up by the National Textile Council, a local textile
company, and the US's AMOCO.
</P>
<P>
Work on the joint venture project started last April, with
government approval. It is expected to produce 250,000 tons of PTA
annually when it starts operating and will help meet the needs of
the burdened domestic PTA market a great deal, according to an
official with the National Textile Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
