<HEADLINE> Travel Association to Start Chinese Training Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Pacific Asia Travel
Association (PATA) has decided to open a Chinese training program
to meet the growing demand for Chinese language study in the
tourism business in Chinese-speaking countries like Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The report comes from the 46th annual conference of PATA being
held in Beijing. The program will be sponsored by PATA's New
Zealand Chapter and will begin in November. The language of
instruction will be Mandarin Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Trainees will be able to greet visitors in Mandarin after a
short course of study, and will be able to use a variety of
cross-cultural skills that are suited to different visitor
markets.
</P>
<P>
The program will also help trainees recognise different
Chinese-speaking markets and develop a plan of action to respond
to market needs.
</P>
<P>
PATA said yesterday in its annual work report that the
Asia-Pacific region is an area with the fastest tourism growth in
the world. 
</P>
