<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak Minister Calls for Combating Desertification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Minister for Food
and Agriculture Syeda Abida Hussain called here today for
concerted efforts to combat desertification in the country.
</P>
<P>
She was speaking at the inaugural session of a three-day
seminar on the implementation of the U.N. Convention on Combating
Desertification.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was organized by the Ministry of Environment, Local
Government and Rural Development in collaboration with the Interim
Secretariat of the U.N. Convention for Combating Desertification.
</P>
<P>
The adoption of the U.N. Convention on Combating
Desertification by Pakistan is of significant importance, Abida
said.
</P>
<P>
"The convention comes as a ray of hope for more than 1 billion
people around the world whose lives are threatened by the adverse
impacts of droughts and desertification," she said.
</P>
<P>
Abida said desertification is an environmental, climatic and
human activity phenomenon leading to land degradation in arid,
semi-arid and dry sub-humid areas worldwide.
</P>
<P>
About 80 percent of the area in Pakistan is arid and semi-arid,
she noted.
</P>
<P>
"The arid coastal strip and mangrove deltaic area are under
increasing environmental stress from reduced freshwater flows,
sewage and industrial pollution and over-exploitation of many
other natural resources. It leaves us with no option except for
making concerted efforts to save country's environment from
further degradation."
</P>
<P>
She observed that the gigantic objective of the implementation
of the convention might be achieved only by adopting a bottom-up
approach.
</P>
<P>
"For this we will have to strengthen local decision-making
mechanism and empower peoples' organizations as non-political
forces to bring a social change right from the grassroots."
</P>
<P>
She concluded with the hope that an action-oriented research
and development plan would be brought out by scientists and
research scholars to combat desertification in Pakistan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
