<HEADLINE> Travel Association to Hold Mekong Tourism Forum in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Pacific Asia Travel
Association (PATA) will hold its second Mekong Tourism Forum in Ho
Chi Minh City on October 30-31, this year, to explore new tourist
venues along the Mekong River.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came at PATA's 46th annual conference which is
being held in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Mekong, or Lancang River on the Chinese side, snakes its
way through Cambodia, China, Laos, Myanmar, Thailand and
Vietnam. It has beautiful scenery and colorful ethnic cultures
along its route, and has become a popular tourist spot. The six
countries want to show their tourism advantages and are trying to
promote tourism in the region.
</P>
<P>
The forum will focus on doing business in this new market and
on how to deal with marketing, packaging, and business
partnerships. It will provide valuable networking and business
opportunities for executives with national tourist organizations,
entrepreneurs, hoteliers, airlines, travel agents, and tour
operators.
</P>
<P>
The forum will be hosted by the Vietnam National Administration
of Tourism in cooperation with the Asian Development Bank and the
Economic and Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific.
</P>
<P>
The first forum was held in Thailand in April 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
