<HEADLINE> Gold Deposits Found in Malawi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Malawi said it has traced gold
deposits in the southern border town of Mwanza and in the
outskirts of the capital Lilongwe.
</P>
<P>
There are also signs of diamonds in the historic town of
Livingstonia in the northern region, according to Africa
Information Afrique.
</P>
<P>
The mineral deposits were identified following an integrated
geographical-geochemical exploration program for gold by the
Department of Geographical Survey of the southern African
country.
</P>
<P>
The program was initiated in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Licences have been awarded to three foreign investors to do
further exploration work and to establish whether the size of the
deposits are worth exploitation.
</P>
<P>
The three foreign companies are OB group of the United States,
Consolidated Diamond of South Africa and the Zambezi Exploration
of Zimbabwe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
