<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-22 08:54 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Has 100,000 Personal Computers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 22 (Xinhua) -- There are around 100,000
personal computers in Kuwait at present and 20,000 computers are
introduced into the country per year, an official was quoted today
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The computer market in Kuwait is estimated at around 35 million
Kuwait dinars (115.5 million U.S. dollars) to 40 million dinars
(132 million dollars), judging by statistics of some global
computer firms, Director General of the Kuwaiti Information Center
and Computer Services and Consultations Mansour Al-Moussa told a
local newspaper.
</P>
<P>
He said computer business in Kuwait rests on three factors
comprising the computer machine, programs and the training and
maintenance services.
</P>
<P>
Although there were no comprehensive statistics to specify the
exact market value, he said, "if we assume that the average price
of a computer is 500 dinars (1,650 U.S. dollars), we can conclude
that annual computer sales come to 10 million dinars (33 million
dollars), together with 20 million dinars (66 million dollars) for
programs and related services and 5 to 10 million dinars for
training and maintenance, the local market would come to 35
million to 40 million dinars."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, member of the Kuwait Computer Society Board Abdul
Aziz Al-Duaij said that 60 percent of the computers sold here
were assembled locally.
</P>
<P>
Computer sold in Kuwaiti markets include a variety of famous
brands produced in the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
