<DOCNO> XIE19970422.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction Work Begins on East China Sea Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, April 22 (Xinhua) -- ground breaking began Monday on a
highway-railway bridge that will connect the Chinese mainland with
Daxie Island near Ningbo City in Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the bridge will have a 1,538-m
four-lane highway and a 1,661.7-m railway on the same level. It
will handle 32,000 vehicles per day.
</P>
<P>
The whole project will take 27 months to finish at a cost of
430 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Daxie Island is one of the most suitable places on China's east
coast for an international bulk cargo center.
</P>
<P>
In November of 1992, Chinese Vice-President Rong Yiren, who was
Chairman of the China International Trust and Investment
Corporation (CITIC), made a decision about large-scale land
development on Daxie. The project got approval from the State
Council in March of 1993 and Daxie Island has been given
preferential treatment of an economic and technological
development zone.
</P>
<P>
The bridge is considered the most important infrastructure to
turn Daxie Island into a first-class port and trade zone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
