<HEADLINE> Poverty-Relief Benefits Farmers in Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUHHOT, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Guo Huaili, a farmer in the Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region, recently moved his ten family members
into two new well-furnished houses by benefitting from an
aid-the-poor project of the local government.
</P>
<P>
"With funding and technology assistance, we devoted ourselves
to our work and our per capita income was 7,000 yuan last year,"
Guo exclaimed.
</P>
<P>
Government officials, Communist Party members, civil servants,
and soldiers of the People's Liberation Army have been involved in
the project, along with private businessmen, college students, and
scientific researchers.
</P>
<P>
Last year, some 680,000 local farmers improved their lives,
bringing the number of people who have shaken off the poverty over
the last ten years to 3.8 million in the autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
The government put 19.8 million yuan into the poverty-relief
drive last year, and has attracted a total of 230 million yuan in
funds for its poverty-relief project.
</P>
<P>
Officials responsible for the poverty-relief work say that the
target for 1997 and 1998 is to help 2.3 million poor farmers
escape poverty, 
</P>
</TEXT>
