<HEADLINE> Mozambican Govt Increases Minimum Wage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican Government
announced today the new lowest wage standard, raising it to
311,794 Meticais (27 U.S. Dollars) in the industrial and
commercial sectors.
</P>
<P>
The minimum wage reached 209,960 Meticais (18.2 Dollars) in
agricultural and stockbreeding sectors in the southern African
country, the Noticias newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
The hike of minimum wage, decided by the government, the
enterprisers and the trade union, took effect on April 1.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican government also increased by 15 percent the
wages of the public servants, the servicemen and the retirees at
the end of March.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique's gross national product (GNP) rose by six percent
to about 1.6 billion U.S. Dollars last year, according to
official data.
</P>
<P>
However, the International Monetary Fund issued a report early
this month saying that per capita income in Mozambique only
stands at 80 Dollars, putting the country at the bottom of the
world list on GNP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
