<HEADLINE> Muslim Reebs Kill Soldier in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Moro Islamic Liberation Front
(MILF) rebels Monday struck anew at government troops in Aleosan,
Cotabato, the southern Philippines, killing a soldier and wounding
another.
</P>
<P>
The attack followed separate MILF offensives in Buldon,
Maguindanao, and Carmen, Cotabato, over the weekend, where one
soldier and 25 rebels were killed, the Philippine News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted Captain Noel Detoyato, spokesman of the
Army's Sixth Infantry Division, as saying the two soldiers were
among a group of government troops that escorted a local
engineering team to repair a road.
</P>
<P>
"They were preparing to leave the area at 4 p.m. when ambushed
by the rebels," Detoyato said.
</P>
<P>
However, Ghadzali Jaafar, MILF vice chief for political
affairs, claimed over a local radio that his men did not provoke
the incident.
</P>
<P>
He said the military entered the area without coordination with
the MILF forces present in the area.
</P>
<P>
"Our men only defended their position thinking that the
military were there to conduct operations against the MILF,"
Jaafar said.
</P>
<P>
The attack occurred two days before the scheduled third round
of preliminary talks between the two sides on April 23-24. Among
the issues to be discussed by peace negotiators is the cessation
of hostilities between the military and the rebels.  
</P>
