<HEADLINE> Guangdong Improves Industrial Structure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 22 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
province has made an effort to optimize its industrial structure
to stimulate economic development.
</P>
<P>
One provincial government official says that three measures
have been taken. The first is to form a series of pillar
industries in petrochemicals, electric power, light industry, and
medicine. The second is to establish over 100 large enterprises
with annual sales revenue reaching three to ten billion yuan, and
the third is to develop brand names for local products to enter
international market.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government is making an effort to increase
technology renovation by spending as much as 30 percent of its
fixed assets on this, working out regulations to encourage
technology renovation, and enhancing technology reforms in 70
major large-scale enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Guangdong has intensifying its efforts in
optimizing regional economic structure. It is undertaking its plan
for coordinated development of the Pearl River Delta and its
northern mountains, and is mapping out plans for coordinated
development of its eastern and western. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
