<HEADLINE> Indian New Prime Minister Seeks Vote of Confidence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- India's new Prime Minister I.
K. Gujral is seeking a vote of confidence in the parliament by
tabling a motion to the lower house for the purpose today.
</P>
<P>
Gujral was sworn in as the country's 12th prime minister by
President S. D. Sharma here Monday, thus ending 22 days of
political uncertainty following the Congress Party's withdrawal of
support to the Deve Gowda government on March 30.
</P>
<P>
The Congress Party had insisted that the 13-party United Front
(UF) should change its leader so as to get back its support and
Gujral has been accepted by the party.
</P>
<P>
The president appointed Gujral as the new prime minister on
April 20 and asked him to show that he has a majority in the
parliament by April 22.  
</P>
