<HEADLINE> New Cable Car for Tourists in Old Chinese Revolutionary Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A cable car has been built in
the Jinggangshan mountains in east China's Jiangxi Province for
sightseeing.
</P>
<P>
It starts at the Longtan (Dragon Pool) and runs to the
Xiannutan (Fairy Maiden Pool), with a 196.8-meter climb. It has 82
cars and can carry 505 persons per hour.
</P>
<P>
The local government raised tens of millions of yuan to build
it to improve the movement of tourists at this sightseeing spot,
which was the major revolutionary base of the Red Army led by the
Chinese Communist Party in the early 1930s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
