<HEADLINE> South Chinese City Intensifies Anti-Drug Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN April 22 (Xinhua) -- The booming border city of
Shenzhen, in south China's Guangdong Province, is intensifying its
crackdown on drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The city plans to announce a campaign to get all citizens to
participate in the anti-drug campaign. Telephone hot-lines will be
set up to encourage people to inform on drug dealers, and a reward
system will also be established for those who have helped in the
crackdown efforts.
</P>
<P>
The city tracked down 426 drug trafficking cases in 1996,
arrested 642 drug smugglers, and seized 647 kg of heroin.
</P>
<P>
It has set up four drug-treatment centers to help addicts kick
their habit, and more than 12,000 drug addicts have been put
through the program in the past five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
