<HEADLINE> Half Multinational Force Entered Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- About half of the European
multinational force has gradually entered Albania since April 15
to protect the humanitarian relief operations and help restore
orders to the nation.
</P>
<P>
The force is made up of 6,230 soldiers from Italy, France,
Greece, Turkey, Spain, Romania, Austria and Denmark, with 2,600 of
them Italians.
</P>
<P>
The force has been deployed in eight main cities of Albania
including capital Tirana, and is mainly to protect airports,
resorts, highways, warehouses and aid materials before July when
the parliamentary election ends.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time a multinational force entering Albania.
</P>
<P>
According to a list prepared by the Albanian government, it is
in bad need of 70,000 tons of wheat, 60,000 tons of flour, 12,000
tons of sugar, 7,000 tons of cooking oil and 5,000 tons of
rice. The aid materials could only meet Albania's needs for 50
days. 
</P>
