<HEADLINE> Life Insurers See Record Growth of Premium Income </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The life insurers in Shanghai,
China's largest trade and financial city, have matched for the
first time their counterparts in property insurance in terms of
premium income.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Insurance Association of Shanghai show that
the total premium income generated from the local insurance market
reached 5.8 billion yuan last year, of which life premium income
accounted for 49.6 percent compared with 39 percent of the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Insurance specialists say that this is the first time the
city's life premium income has matched that from property
insurance.
</P>
<P>
The premium income from the local insurance market will keep
ballooning in the coming years, thanks to the stable growth of the
national economy and the annual income of residents, experts say.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, one of the two pilot cities open to overseas
insurers, has seen a sharp expansion of local insurance market
over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the city's total life premium income rose
by 67.8 percent from that in 1995, much higher than the city's
average 32 percent in the whole sector of insurance.
</P>
<P>
The city has also established a large team of insurance sales
agents, whose number has reached 18,000 now, and has kept
increasing by 1,000 per month.
</P>
<P>
Insurance experts say that life insurers will soon beat their
counterparts in property insurance, and win a overwhelming share
of the total premium income of local insurance market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
