<HEADLINE> Argentine Wine Wins World Prize In Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Nieto &AMP; Senetiner, an
Argentine winery, won the Vinitaly 1997 prize at the international
oenological competition held in Verona, Italy where Argentine
wines garnered 14 prizes in different categories.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time since 1995 that the Nieto &AMP; Senetiner
winery won the great gold medal (the maximum award) with the wine
known as "Vinas de Santa Isabel Doc Malbec," informed sources from
the Industry, Commerce and Mining Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The award-winning wine is the first wine from the American
continent and of that typical Argentine variety to achieve the
designation of controlled origin or DOC. 
