<HEADLINE> Ninth Andean Presidential Council To Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUCRE, BOLIVIA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The ninth Andean
Presidential Council will meet here Tuesday to sign the Sucre Act,
which sets up a system of permanent dialogue between China and the
Andean group.
</P>
<P>
The two-day council meeting will be attended by Bolivian
President Gonzalo Lozada, Colombian President Ernesto Samper,
Ecuadoran President Fabian Alarcon and Venezuelan President Rafael
Caldera as well as government ministers.
</P>
<P>
Panamanian President Ernesto Perez Balladares and Paraguayan
President Juan Carlos Wasmosy will also be present as guests.
</P>
<P>
However, Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori, who decided to
withdraw from the bloc unless the other four members stopped
pressing Peru to reduce its customs duty to zero, will not attend
the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Peru accused the members, which had already introduced
duty-free policy in the group, of providing subsidies to their
export products to Peru.
</P>
<P>
The future trade ties between Peru and other member states will
be another major topic of the summit.
</P>
<P>
The Andean group will be named as the Andean Community after
the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
