<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Congratulates Pacific Fleet Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
sent a telegram today to Admiral Vladimir Kuroyedov, the commander
of the Pacific Fleet, congratulating its 65th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said in the telegram "soldiers of the Pacific Fleet
have written many vivid pages in the history of the Fatherland and
earned immortal glory in the battles of the Great Patriotic War,"
the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
He added, "the Pacific Fleet, continuing its best traditions,
is on vigil, reliably protecting Russia's security in the Far
East."
</P>
<P>
The Pacific fleet, one of the most powerful formations in the
Russian armed forces, was founded on April 21, 1932 when the naval
forces of the Far East were formed under the Soviet
government.
</P>
<P>
It has made remarkable contributions to the Great Patriotic War
of the Soviet Union, with 43 members awarded the title of Soviet
Hero.  
