<HEADLINE> Four Die in Storm in Paraguay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Four people died in a
tropical storm which struck the Paraguayan capital Asuncion over
the weekend, reports from Paraguay said.
</P>
<P>
Two of them were crushed under the roofs of their houses and
the other two died after being electrocuted, the Paraguayan police
said.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that in the power sector alone, property damage
was estimated at 700,000 U.S. dollars nationwide. Unofficial
estimates of the total losses topped 1.5 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The storm came a week after the most destructive storm in the
region for 16 years destroyed about 2,000 trees and 40 minor
electricity sub-stations in Asuncion. 
</P>
