<DOCNO> XIE19970422.0261 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama, World Leader In Ship Registrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Panama is number one in the
world for ship registrations with 13,625 ships registered in
Panama up to the end of the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Between January-March, Panama registered 248 mercantile ships
and received revenues of 19.7 million dollars, an increase of 14.5
percent over the same period in 1996, said a report from the
consular and ship registration division of the Finance and
Treasury Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The gross weight of ships during the first quarter rose to 4.6
million gross tons and the overall to 107.8 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Of the number of ships registered between January-March, 101
are new and 60 percent of new ships prefer to register in Panama.
</P>
<P>
Panama expects to register 500 ships this year, according to
the Planning and Economic Policy Ministry budget.
</P>
<P>
As the world leader in ship registrations, Panama occupies a
privileged position in the International Maritime Organization
(IMO) to which it contributes 13.5 percent of its budget,
according to Panamanian authorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
