<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German, Italian Presidents Discuss Social Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Italian President Oscar
Luigi Scalfaro met his German counterpart Roman Herzog today in
Berlin with discussions focusing on fundamental reforms in the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Herzog told reporters after the meeting that while Germany was
making great efforts to reform its taxation and social welfare
systems, Italy was giving top priority to overhaul its state
institutions.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the difficulties of social welfare states were
obvious in both countries, Scalfaro stressed that social reforms
must result in changes during which the weak group of the
population should be taken into consideration.
</P>
<P>
In combating unemployment, economic growth alone cannot solve
the problem, Scalfaro said after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Italian president started his four-day visit to Germany on
Sunday in the eastern cities of Erfurt and Weimar. He is due in
Bonn on Wednesday to meet German Chancellor Helmut Kohl and Rita
Suessmuth, President of the German Bundestag, the lower house of
the parliament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
