<HEADLINE> Mediterranean Symposium on Red Meat Opens in Tunis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Mediterranean symposium on red
meat opened here today with participation of some 100 experts.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the international center of higher agricultural
studies for Mediterranean states, the symposium is attended by
experts on the red meat from France, Italy, Algeria, Morocco,
Egypt, Spain, Syria, Portugal, Turkey, Greece, Lebanon and Tunisia.
</P>
<P>
It aims at exchanging expertise among the Mediterranean
establishments and setting up an information network among them.
</P>
<P>
It also aims at developing a plan of research and action among
the Mediterranean establishments and foundation of a regional
Mediterranean center of the red meat sector.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of the three-day symposium includes discussion of
diverse items in four workshops, the first to deal with methods of
cattle breeding, the second with manufacturing industries and
technology, while the third and fourth workshops are respectively
concerned with marketing and national organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
