<HEADLINE> Clinton Plans to Visit Flooded Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 21 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
planned to view flood damage and meet victims in North Dakota
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Clinton planned to visit victims at the Air Force base in Grand
Forks, N.D., and take a helicopter tour of flooding in North
Dakota and Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
White House chief of staff Erskine Bowles reportedly planned to
host a meeting this afternoon with members of Congress from the
Dakotas and Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
National Weather Service officials said the Red River was
expected to crest today at Grand Forks at 54 feet, 26 feet above
flood stage.
</P>
<P>
New reports said most of the 50,000 residents of Grand Forks
have left their city under a mandatory evacuation order issued by
city officials, who predict the 54-foot crest could last for
several days and possibly a week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
