<HEADLINE> Camerounian President Nominates New Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Camerounian President Paul Biya
nominated on Monday Edoundi Charles as the Minister of Pulic Health of
Cameroun to replace Titus Edzoa, who resigned last Sunday,
according to a presidential decree declared here today.
</P>
<P>
The nomination was made on the recommendation of Prime
Minister Peter Mafany Musonge.
</P>
<P>
Edoundi Charles is the principal of a school named "Lycee Leclerc
de Yaounde". He never works in the government before this nomination.
He is not doctor.
</P>
<P>
Titus Eduzoa, a famous doctor in Cameroun, declared his
resignation in the Yaounde Hilton Hotel yesterday morming indicating
that he would take part in the presidential elections late this year.
