<HEADLINE> Environmental Education Initiative Launched in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The initiative known as the
"Cameroun Environmental Education Support Project" (CCESP) was
launched here today.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the European Union and the Living Earth
Foundation, the project is to promote environmental awareness on
education in schools and local communities in Cameroun.
</P>
<P>
When officially launching the event this morning, Yunga
Teghen, the Secretary of State for National Education of Cameroun,
said the introduction of the environmental education (EE) in
school is in confirmity with the government's environmental
management policy.
</P>
<P>
The project seeks to provide information and EE resources for
individuals and local initiatives involved in the promotion of
sustainable use of natural resources.
</P>
<P>
The commissioning of the project is expected to be done by the
Ministry of National Education and will be followed by a workshop
during which a common understanding of project and participating
strategy will be discussed. End

