<HEADLINE> UAE-Japan Trade Grows by 13 percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Trade between the United Arab
Emirates (UAE) and Japan in 1996 grew by 13 percent to reach 13.9
billion US dollars, compared with 12.3 billion dollars in 1995,
the UAE's Wam news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The exports of UAE to Japan increased by 12.6 percent to
11.4501 billion dollars, compared with 10.1723 billion dollars in
the previous year, while While UAE's imports from Japan grew by 10
percent to 2.3 billion dollars, compared with 1995's 2.1 billion
dollars, Wam said.
</P>
<P>
The UAE's trade with Japan covers about 37 percent of Japan's
total 37.5-billion-dollar trade with the oil-rich Gulf Cooperation
Council (GCC) states which groups Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, Oman,
Qatar, Bahrain and the UAE.
</P>
<P>
This has turned the UAE the largest Gulf trade market
for Japan, whose global trade were valued at 735.1 billion
dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Detailing the UAE-Japan trade, Wam said that Japan is the
biggest importer of the UAE's fuel products in 1996 when the
eastern-Asian country purchased 11.3421 billion dollars of crude
oil, natural gas and other kind of fuel, occupying 98 percent of
its total imports from the UAE.
</P>
<P>
It bought 449.4 million barrels of the UAE's crude oil last
year, worth 7.3465 billion dollars, keeping the same level
of 1995's 449.3 million barrels.
</P>
<P>
The average crude oil price stood at 16.8 dollars per
barre in 1995 and some 16.5 dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The crude oil provided by the UAE, the world fourth
largest oil producer met 28.2 percent of the total crude oil
need of Japan in 1996, Wam said.
</P>
<P>
Natural gas imports by Japan stood at 707 million dollars
in 1996, a 12.9 percent growth compared with 626.4 million in
1995, Wam added.
</P>
<P>
Japan also imported from the UAE mineral products, which
represented some 1.5 percent of its last year's total imports
from the Gulf country.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, it bought 170.5 million dollars of aluminum from
the UAE, a marginal growth compared with 169.4 million
dollar s in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Referring to UAE's imports from Japan, Wam said that industry
equipment and machines consisted of the biggest part of the
imports in 1996, when the equipment and machine imports reached
1.68 billion dollars, compared with 1.5 billion in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Imports of electrical appliance from Japan grew by 3.1 percent
to 562.1 million dollars, compared with 545 million dollars in
1995. The auto imports reached 434.1 million dollars and ship
imports valued at 132.1 million dollars, Wam said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Japanese also exported to the UAE
telecommunications equipment, video equipment and electronic
components.
</P>
<P>
Wam said that the UAE is the fourth largest market in the world
for these Japanese products in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
